Reguli. M. Atilius Regulus was taken prisoner, by the Cartha- ginians, with 500 of his men B. c. 255. He was sent to Rome to offer terms of peace or an exchange of captives, but he advised the senate to resuse both offers and himself returned to captivity. There are two forms of this story, differing in details. One is related by Cicero de

Off 111. 27, the other by Livy or rather by the person who wrote the epitome of Livy's 18th Book.
